title: Personal opinions on detective pikachu
body:
I know I’m going to get a lot of hate for this but I’m not a fan of how the Pokémon look.

I’m just not a fan of hyperrealism, sorry. It’s not my style. Hyperrealism is something we already see 24/7 in our own world, it’s just dull and boring.

I wish they could look more cartoony. I personally don’t care if it doesn’t look realistic. It’s the whole point of a cartoon fantasy franchise in my opinion.

I’m really not a fan of Pokémon becoming more adult in nature. It kills the spirit. The reason we (or at least I) like Pokémon is BECAUSE it’s a childhood fantasy. Of course adults like me can like Pokémon too, but we like it because of the childhood whimsy. Making it “realistic and gritty” ruins that.

Even Pikachu himself doesn’t even look cute in my honest opinion, more like a plush doll of a gremlin.

Call me a coward but I much prefer the first image over the second.

summary:
I went to Target to get my hands on the exclusive Aggretsuko POP! Figures.
And just cause I like to browse the toys I went...
body:
I went to Target to get my hands on the exclusive Aggretsuko POP! Figures.

And just cause I like to browse the toys I went wandering to the toy aisle

I was almost laser guided to the Detective Pikachu toys

Minus the eyes, these plushies were really good looking, especially the snubbull one that I almost bought it

But the best part was how goddamn soft they were

If you like soft things I highly recommend getting one of the plush toys. Unless you find the eyes just too off putting cause I can see how that would be a problem

I probably should have taken pictures but you can probably just look it up

The material and colors they use reflect the movie designs very well, and it just made me more excited to see the movie
